+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RC4oDie7wZoj32roG5hwgG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me understand the algorithms needed before writing tests.\n\n**Part 1 (Toggle Puzzle):** Each button is a binary variable (0/1). Each light's final state is the XOR of buttons that affect it. We need to solve a system of linear equations over GF(2) (binary field). With up to 40 buttons, brute force is impossible, but Gaussian elimination over GF(2) works.\n\n**Part 2 (Counter Puzzle):** Same idea but over GF(p) where p is a prime modulus. Gaussian elimination over GF(p).\n\nBoth reduce to solving Ax = b over a finite field."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":274,"cache_read_input_tokens":27627,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":274},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f6edb16-70f4-49ff-9463-920191147b82","uuid":"12a793e3-f2e1-4663-beb4-73ac38391014"}
